38

).

Male
. 
Genitalia
. Pygofer lobe with ventromedial process, apex asymmetrically biramous (
Figs 36, 40
); lobe subapically with medial elongate band of macrosetae (
Figs 36, 40
); anterior apodeme large (
Figs 35, 36
). Aedeagal shafts widely separated, inner margins denticulate (
Figs 38, 39
). Plate narrowly triangular, without macrosetae, but short, fine setae, mainly at apex (

Fig. 
37

), lateral subapical margin rugose. Style with elongate, acuminate apophysis, tooth medioventrally; preapical angle deep, rounded; preapical lobe acute; lateral anterior lobe large, wide, right-angled, medial anterior lobe short, triangular (

Fig. 
34

).
